        "\n",
        "## 🧠 Concept: The Transformer Revolution\n",
        "\n",
        "The **Transformer** architecture, introduced in the paper \"Attention Is All You Need\" (2017), revolutionized NLP by replacing recurrent networks with attention mechanisms.\n",
        "\n",
        "### Why Transformers?\n",
        "\n",
        "**Before Transformers (RNNs/LSTMs):**\n",
        "- Sequential processing (slow)\n",
        "- Difficulty with long-range dependencies\n",
        "- Limited parallelization\n",
        "\n",
        "**With Transformers:**\n",
        "- Parallel processing (fast)\n",
        "- Direct connections between all positions\n",
        "- Scalable to massive datasets\n",
        "\n",
        "### The Big Picture\n",
        "\n",
        "```\n",
        "Input Text → Encoder → Context Representation → Decoder → Output Text\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "**Key Components:**\n",
        "1. **Multi-Head Attention:** Focus on different parts of the input\n",
        "2. **Feed-Forward Networks:** Process information independently\n",
        "3. **Layer Normalization:** Stabilize training\n",
        "4. **Residual Connections:** Enable deep networks\n",
        "5. **Positional Encoding:** Capture sequence order\n",
        "\n",
        "---"
      ]
